Consider the following threads T_1, T_2, and T_3 executing on a single processor, synchronized using three binary semaphore variables S_1, S_2, and S_3, operated upon using standard wait() and signal(). The threads can be context switched in any order and at any time.

T_1:
while(true){
  wait(S_1);
  print("A");
  signal(S_2);
}

T_2:
while(true){
  wait(S_2);
  print("B");
  signal(S_3);
}

T_3:
while(true){
  wait(S_3);
  print("C");
  signal(S_1);
}

Which initialization of the semaphores would print the sequence ABCABCABC...?

A. S_1=1, S_2=1, S_3=0
B. S_1=1, S_2=0, S_3=0
C. S_1=0, S_2=0, S_3=0
D. S_1=0, S_2=1, S_3=1

Consider the two functions incr() and decr() shown below.

incr(){
  wait(s);
  X = X + 1;
  signal(s);
}

decr(){
  wait(s);
  X = X - 1;
  signal(s);
}

There are m = 5 threads each invoking incr() once, and n = 3 threads each invoking decr() once, on the same shared variable X. The initial value of X is 10.

Suppose there are two implementations of the semaphore s as follows:
I-1: s is a binary semaphore initialized to 1.
I-2: s is a counting semaphore initialized to 2.

Which one of the following choices corresponds to the minimum possible values of X at the end of execution of all the threads with implementations I-1 and I-2, respectively?

A. 15, 7
B. 7, 15
C. 12, 7
D. 7, 12

The wait and signal operations of a monitor are implemented using semaphores as follows. In the following:
- z is a condition variable
- mutex is a semaphore initialized to 1
- z_sem is a semaphore initialized to 0
- z_count is the number of processes waiting on z_sem, initially 0
- next is a semaphore initialized to 0
- next_count is the number of processes waiting on next, initially 0

The body of each procedure visible outside the monitor is replaced with:
if (next_count > 0) V(next); else V(mutex);

Each occurrence of wait(z) is replaced with:
z_count = z_count + 1;
if (next_count > 0) V(next); else V(mutex);
E1;
z_count = z_count - 1;

Each occurrence of signal(z) is replaced with:
if (z_count > 0) {
  next_count = next_count + 1;
  E2;
  next_count = next_count - 1;
}

For correct implementation of the monitor, E1 and E2 are, respectively:

A. P(z_sem), V(mutex)
B. V(next), P(z_sem)
C. P(z_sem), V(next_count)
D. P(z_sem), V(z_sem)
